					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">BLEP (band-limited step) resampling, the technique used by blip-buf, is a way to eliminate aliasing from a signal when downsampling from the 1.79 MHz CPU frequency to 44100 or 48000 or whatever target frequency. It works by decomposing a signal into a sum of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heaviside_step_function" class="postlink">Heaviside steps</a>, low-pass filtering a single representative step, sampling that filtered step at various fractions of an output sample, and adding up all the steps. For example, a square wave at 250 Hz has 500 steps per second: 250 rises and 250 falls.</div><br /><br />Thank you very much <br />This is something very useful</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Peace Synthesizer Framework<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://peacedeveloper.appspot.com/docs/PeaceSynthesizerFramework/html/index.html">http://peacedeveloper.appspot.com/docs/ ... index.html</a><!-- m --></div>
